{
  "stem": "24111.7",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When you-- when you open it up, every government issuing it-- in my case, it was-- in our case, it was the Swiss government-- issues a statement that this and this person is an Austrian citizen or Norwegian citizen, Polish citizen, Dutch citizen, born so-and-so, and-- and all the-- [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it is only good-- good, valid, for one-- one-way travel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Which means you could exit, but you could never enter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And on one-- on one part of the paper are all your [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] documented entries.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On the other side of the paper is the British Mandate certificate stamp and the exit visas and also the entry visas.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we received, each one of us, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Nansen pass, we also received the legal way of leaving Switzerland-- Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the Swiss Jewish community paid the way from [FRENCH] to Barcelona.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Barcelona, we were took-- we were taken over from the joint-- the Jewish organization there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There entered a small ship by the name of an Portuguese tramp ship, you know, one of the small boats.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that brought us to-- to Haifa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Haifa-- you must understand our group was-- was at that time 300.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we collected now Jews from all over France, from all the camps in-- [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were brought to a-- to an-- to a point in Barcelona, a collecting point.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when this ship going to-- to Palestine, to Haifa, was full to the capacity, I would say it was perhaps 700 people, including our group of 300.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It sailed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was August '95.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ah, '45, I beg your pardon, 1945.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And in Palestine, we were the first legal immigrants.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
